Description:
SURE TO IMPRESS

A spacious lounge with timber look floors adjoining the dining area with split system & gas heater.
Neutral coloured tiles, freshly painted throughout & plenty of storage cupboards.
Outside a large undercover entertaining area with slate tiles. A carport with drive through access to the backyard with garden shed and ample yard space.
On an approx 800m2 block in a quiet street walking distance to the school, sporting facilities & shops.

Description:
Desirable location
Located in the sought after Sturt Street, there is more than meets the eye with this family home. Upon entry you have the formal lounge/dining area that has a gorgeous bay window. You then walk through the kitchen that overlooks the family/meals and comprises electric wall oven, gas cooktop, dishwasher and ample storage for all your household needs. The master bedroom is located at the rear of the home and has an ensuite with shower, vanity and toilet and a large sized walk in robe. The remaining three bedrooms all have built in robes and share the family bathroom. Ducted throughout the home is gas ducted heating and evaporative cooling. There is also direct access from the double garage directly into the home making it ideal for those security conscious buyers. Externally there is a sensational outdoor entertaining area that spans almost the length of the home making it ideal for those who love to entertain. The rear yard is a good size and offers a garden shed. This home is in a desirable location and has a lot on offer and deserves an inspection.

A fantastic spot to build your dream home, walk the dog by the water or fish the day away. It is very rare to find vacant land such as this so close to the river. In-town convenience with all the peace and serenity of living amongst the Murray River bush land.

Description:
Why build?
This brick veneer home offers three bedrooms and open plan living. The galley kitchen has stainless steel appliances including gas cooktop, underbench oven and dishwasher and overlooks the meals and lounge area. The master bedroom has walk in robe and ensuite with separate shower, vanity and toilet. The remaining two bedrooms offer built in robes. The family bathroom has separate bath, shower compartment and vanity. Climate throughout is controlled by gas ducted heating and split system to lounge/meals area. Externally there is an outdoor entertaining area, double garage and small rear yard. For investors, this property has been previously rented out at between $310 - $320 per week. Why be inconvenienced with building a brand new home when this one is only a few years old and ready to be moved into today! Worth an inspection.
